## 1. Executive Summary

**FairBanks** is a community health ecosystem — **FairBanks Community Reach**, medical centre, CHWs/VHTs, **CHIS** (Community Health Insurance Scheme), partnerships, livelihoods, and research — evolving into **Africa's leading Community Health Intelligence Company**.

**FCHIP** (FairBanks Community Health Intelligence Platform) is a **core FairBanks component**: the deep-technology intelligence layer on the Community Reach cascade. It connects community members, CHWs/VHTs, schools, communities, hospitals, clinics, outreach programmes, and public-health decision-makers into one intelligent network — powering the **Data & Feedback** loop shown in the concept visuals. FCHIP will also **safely expose data APIs to existing EMR/HMS systems** so facilities can share clinical records into the platform in real time — without replacing the systems clinics already use.

Today, primary healthcare in underserved African communities is largely **reactive**: facilities treat patients only after illness appears, with little visibility into what is happening in surrounding villages until outbreaks, complications, or stock-outs occur. Through FCHIP, FairBanks continuously analyses multi-source health data and combines it with **GIS mapping and climate APIs** to forecast disease risk, maternal complications, chronic-disease hotspots, child-health threats, climate-linked outbreaks, and medicine demand **before** crises escalate — moving communities along the theory of change: **Participation → Prevention → Access → Earlier care → Better health → Livelihoods → Learning → Better services**.

FairBanks is uniquely positioned to build and validate this. We already operate a functioning medical centre, run active Community Reach across Kampala peri-urban areas (Bukoto, Kyebando, Kisaasi, Kamwokya, Kikaaya, and surrounding communities), work with VHTs and CHWs, and deliver maternal and child health, geriatric care (Gericare), chronic-disease screening, corporate and school health programmes, digital health records, CHIS financial protection, livelihood/IGA support, and research partnerships. FCHIP is the FairBanks technology component that unifies these activities into a scalable, evidence-driven health intelligence system.

**Vision:** To build Africa's leading Community Health Intelligence Company — FairBanks — whose FCHIP component harnesses artificial intelligence, community-generated data, GIS, climate signals, and predictive analytics to transform primary healthcare from reactive treatment to proactive prevention — while strengthening the Community Reach loop of care, learning, and empowerment.

**Funding ask (indicative):** Support to validate and scale the working FCHIP MVP within FairBanks Community Reach—mobile data collection for CHWs/VHTs, cloud sync, secure EMR/HMS data APIs for real-time clinical ingest, GIS and climate API integration, predictive analytics engine, and facility/district dashboards—proven in FairBanks' live cascade (communities → CHWs → programmes → medical centre → research → empowerment) before district and regional scale-up.

