## 13. Application-Ready Copy Blocks

*Use the sections below when completing grant, accelerator, or investor applications. Swap in the call name and word limits as needed.*

### 13.1 One-line pitch

FairBanks is a Community Health Intelligence Company built on Community Reach (care, CHWs, medical centre, CHIS, livelihoods); FCHIP — its core platform component — uses AI, GIS, and climate APIs with community and facility data to turn African primary healthcare from reactive treatment to proactive prevention.

### 13.2 Problem (short form)

Underserved African communities lack real-time health intelligence. Facilities treat sickness after it appears, while data from CHWs, schools, communities, hospitals, and clinics stays fragmented — climate signals rarely join the picture, and clinical records often stay locked in facility EMR/HMS systems — so the Community Reach feedback loop cannot learn fast enough to prevent outbreaks, maternal complications, or stock-outs.

### 13.3 Solution (short form)

FairBanks' FCHIP component sits on the Community Reach cascade: it ingests multi-source health data (CHW/VHT, schools, communities, hospitals, clinics), safely exposes data APIs to existing EMR/HMS systems for real-time clinical capture, fuses signals with GIS maps and climate APIs, and delivers predictive alerts and dashboards so facilities, districts, and partners can act before crises escalate — while strengthening CHIS, livelihoods, and continuous improvement.

### 13.4 Why now

Mobile penetration, CHW networks, open climate data, and cloud infrastructure make community health intelligence deployable at scale — FairBanks already runs Community Reach in Kampala peri-urban communities; FCHIP completes the Data & Feedback technology layer.

### 13.5 Unique value proposition

Only venture combining a **live medical centre, Community Reach cascade (incl. CHIS and livelihoods)**, and a **deep-tech predictive health platform** (GIS + climate + multi-source FCHIP analysis) — allowing real-world design, pilot, and validation before district and national scale. Visual model: `.cursor/concept_improved.jpeg`.

